{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"f98f4eec-47b9-4b97-aeb8-79a5739d5890","content":"Yes, you'll hit compatibility issues. Here's what matters:\n\n**Framework support dropped in MSTest v3:**\n\n| Target | Status |\n|---|---|\n| `net462` | ✅ Supported (minimum is net462) |\n| `netcoreapp3.1` | ❌ **Dropped** — out of support |\n| `net5.0` | ❌ **Dropped** — out of support |\n\nYou'll need to update `netcoreapp3.1` and `net5.0` to supported frameworks like `net6.0` or `net8.0`.\n\n**Other notable MSTest v3 changes:**\n- **Package consolidation** — you can replace the separate `MSTest.TestFramework` + `MSTest.TestAdapter` references with a single `MSTest` meta-package.\n- **Behavioral breaking changes** — stricter timeout defaults, `TestContext` API changes, and some assert method behavior differences.\n\n**Minimal migration** would look like updating your `TargetFrameworks` and packages:\n\n```xml\n<TargetFrameworks>net8.0;net462</TargetFrameworks>\n...\n<PackageReference Include=\"MSTest\" Version=\"3.7.3\" />\n<PackageReference Include=\"Microsoft.NET.Test.Sdk\" Version=\"17.5.0\" />\n```\n\nWould you like me to apply these changes?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"acfe1027-215d-420c-b6f9-2add585e08f0","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is multi-targeting `net5.0`, `net462`, and `netcoreapp3.1`. MSTest v3 dropped support for some older frameworks. Let me provide accurate information about compatibility issues.\n\nMSTest v3 (starting with 3.x) has the following key compatibility changes:\n\n1. **Dropped .NET Framework < 4.6.2** — but they have net462 which is exactly 4.6.2, so that should be fine.\n2. **Dropped .NET Core 3.1** — MSTest v3 dropped support for `netcoreapp3.1`. This is a problem.\n\n\n3. **Dropped .NET 5.0** — .NET 5.0 is out of support and MSTest v3 does not support it either.\n\nSo the user will face compatibility issues with both `net5.0` and `netcoreapp3.1` and needs to update those target frameworks to supported versions like `net6.0` or `net8.0`. MSTest v3 also consolidated its packages, so they can use the single `MSTest` meta-package instead of managing separate `MSTest.TestFramework` and `MSTest.TestAdapter` packages.\n\nBeyond that, there are several breaking changes to be aware of: some assert APIs have different behavior now, `TestContext` has been modified, and the timeout behavior for class and assembly cleanup has changed.","outputTokens":660,"requestId":"981D:1CF7FE:128BE5B:176DC00:69FFF2F0"},"id":"f333ae06-9946-4ddc-ad9a-f83fc0f75314","timestamp":"2026-05-10T02:52:46.371Z","parentId":"c368c3fe-2c9b-44a8-842a-32f0d7f87e65"}
